title: The Tchaikovsky Experience, Vol. 2 - Dutoit, MSO
description:
"The Tchaikovsky Experience" is a five disc compilation of Tchaikovsky's compositions recorded by the Montreal Symphony Orchestra, conducted by Charles Dutoit, in the 1980s and early 90s and released by Decca in 1993.

The volumes contain the following compositions:

VOLUME I
Swan Lake: Highlights, The Sleeping Beauty: Polonaise, The Nutcracker: Suite, Marche slave.

VOLUME II
Piano Concerto No. 1, Violin Concerto.

VOLUME III
Capriccio italien, Symphony No. 4, 1812 Overture.

VOLUME IV
Symphony No. 5, Francesca da Rimini.

VOLUME V
Symphony No. 6, Romeo and Juliet.

Please enjoy.
